                     <interp inst="t17700912-38-person384" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             who had known him 7 years; 
               <persName id="t17700912-38-person385">
                  Wm.
                   Holford
               <interp inst="t17700912-38-person385" type="surname" value="Holford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700912-38-person385" type="given" value="Wm."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700912-38-person385" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             16 years; 
               <persName id="t17700912-38-person386">
                  Tho.
                   Cross
               <interp inst="t17700912-38-person386" type="surname" value="Cross"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700912-38-person386" type="given" value="Tho."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700912-38-person386" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             20 years, and - Davis 16 or 17 years, who spoke of his having lived <rs id="t17700912-38-deflabel195" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17700912-38-defend374 t17700912-38-deflabel195"></join> to several noblemen, and always having had a good character.</p>
